# Only The Inherited Suitable-Weak / Leray-Hopf Plus LEI Floor Has A Locally Frozen Theorem Endpoint

Status: `VERIFIED` Step-008 framework-freeze result

The Step-008 setup menu leaves exactly one serious framework alive for the
beyond-De Giorgi compactness-rigidity branch.

What is locally frozen:

- suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with the local energy
  inequality;
- divergence-free velocity with
  `u in L^\infty_t L^2_x \cap L^2_t H^1_x`;
- pressure handled in the suitable-weak sense;
- the localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle
  `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u . nabla phi`;
- and the CKN quantities `A(r)`, `E(r)`, `C(r)`, and `D(r)` as the fixed
  bookkeeping language.

Within that inherited floor, the only locally supported theorem-level
cash-out line is the CKN/Lin epsilon-regularity contradiction package:
endpoint-regularity exclusion on the LEI floor.

So Step-008 does not earn a new framework. It freezes the inherited one as the
only coherent setup that is actually tied to a theorem endpoint in the local
record.

